const faqs = [
  { q: "Masterpiece vs Professional — which Thermador wall oven line is which?", a: "Thermador's wall oven lineup is split into two product tiers with different positioning. <b>Masterpiece Series</b> is the current flagship tier — modern integrated-kitchen aesthetic, flush-mount installation, updated control platform, available in 30\" and 36\" single + double configurations. Masterpiece is where Thermador competes with Wolf M Series and Miele H 7000 at the ultra-luxury wall-oven level. <b>Professional Series</b> is the mid-tier — pro-style handles + heavier commercial-aesthetic design language, also 30\" and 36\" configurations. Professional positions below Masterpiece in LA's current new-construction spec work but has a large install base from kitchen renovations across the 2010s. Both tiers share BSH's Irvine CA parts-chain distribution advantage; parts interchange at the component level between Masterpiece and Professional for bake elements, sensors, door hardware, and many control-board sub-variants." },
  { q: "What's Sapphire Steam and how is service different?", a: "Sapphire Steam is Thermador's signature steam oven — a distinct wall-oven category combining pure steam cooking capability with traditional convection in a built-in form factor. Sapphire Steam runs on a dedicated steam-generation system (internal water reservoir + boiler element + steam distribution) that mainstream Masterpiece + Professional wall ovens don't have. Service on Sapphire Steam includes: water reservoir descaling on LA hard-water service cadence (similar to Miele Combi-Steam and Wolf CSO), steam-boiler element service, descale cycle firmware (Thermador control logic tracks cycle hours and prompts descale), steam-distribution valve service, and combi-mode switching logic when units run steam + convection combined cycles. Descaling service $260-$420 typical; boiler element replacement $480-$780; steam distribution valve $320-$540. Annual descaling is the right cadence for LA households running Sapphire Steam regularly." },
  { q: "Is Thermador owned by the same company as Bosch or Gaggenau?", a: "Yes — Thermador, Bosch, and Gaggenau are all BSH Hausgeräte brands. BSH (Bosch + Siemens Hausgeräte) is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Robert Bosch GmbH since 2015, and the BSH brand portfolio covers Bosch (mainstream premium), Thermador (luxury US positioning), Gaggenau (ultra-luxury global), and Siemens (European mainstream, limited US presence). The shared BSH parent matters operationally for LA service: all three brands route parts through BSH's Irvine CA US headquarters and distribution, which is a genuine LA-local advantage — parts lead times on BSH brands run shorter than on Sub-Zero Group (Wisconsin), Middleby (Tennessee + Mississippi), or Miele (New Jersey) brands because the distribution warehouse is in SoCal. For LA customers with a Thermador wall oven + Bosch dishwasher + Gaggenau cooktop combination, the shared BSH parts-chain is unified through Irvine CA." },
  { q: "Thermador flush-mount installation — what service discipline does that require?", a: "Thermador Masterpiece wall ovens are engineered for flush-mount integration with surrounding cabinetry, similar in intent to Miele's integrated-kitchen aesthetic. Current Masterpiece spec assumes the unit sits flush with cabinet face; gap lines top/bottom/left/right should be consistent; and the cabinetry surrounding the unit is often custom-panel or color-matched on premium LA remodels. Our Thermador service approach preserves flush-mount integrity through every service call — partial-pull method for service access rather than default full-pull, cabinet-preservation pads during any pull-work to prevent scratching custom panels, shim adjustment at reinstall via the mounting brackets, gap-line verification at all four edges before finishing. Professional Series doesn't require as tight a flush-mount discipline as Masterpiece (the Pro-style design intentionally protrudes slightly from cabinet face), but we maintain alignment tolerance appropriate to the unit's original install spec." },
  { q: "What does Thermador wall oven repair cost in LA?", a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Typical Thermador wall oven service: BSH Irvine parts advantage generally gives slightly faster turnaround than other luxury brands but pricing reflects luxury-tier parts chain. Bake element (Masterpiece or Professional) $380-$620; convection fan motor $440-$720; control board (Masterpiece current generation) $540-$880; temperature sensor $280-$440; door hinge $300-$500; door glass $420-$720; thermostat $340-$540; Sapphire Steam descaling $260-$420; Sapphire Steam boiler element $480-$780; Sapphire Steam distribution valve $320-$540; double wall oven per-cavity service $420-$780; dual-cavity control board $620-$1,020. BSH Irvine distribution runs 1-2 days on common Thermador parts — genuine LA-local advantage over out-of-state-sourced luxury brands." },
  { q: "Do you service Thermador wall ovens installed in kitchens with Bosch or Gaggenau appliances?", a: "Yes — mixed BSH-family kitchens are common in LA premium remodels and we service them as unified customer accounts. Typical LA pattern: Thermador Masterpiece wall oven + Thermador rangetop or cooktop + Bosch dishwasher + sometimes a Gaggenau specialty appliance (Vario cooktop, combi-steam). The shared BSH Irvine parts-chain means we can route parts for all three brands through the same distributor network, coordinate service visits to handle multiple items on one dispatch where the failure mix allows, and apply consistent technical conventions across the family. One distinction worth flagging: Bosch wall oven specifically is classified by our scope as mention-only (per cluster-05 Decision 3 — Bosch's US wall oven lineup didn't hit our dedicated-page threshold). For Bosch wall oven service, see the general Bosch brand hub — service is still covered, just not via a dedicated combo page." }
];

