    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Sapphire Steam — Thermador's signature steam oven service</h2>
    <p>Sapphire Steam is Thermador's entry into the combi-steam luxury category, competing directly with Miele DGC Combi-Steam and Wolf CSO. Like its luxury competitors, Sapphire Steam uses an internal water reservoir + boiler element + steam-distribution system that requires LA hard-water descaling cadence — typically annual for households running Sapphire Steam regularly. Thermador's control logic tracks cycle hours and prompts descale at thresholds; operators should run descaling at the reminder rather than deferring.</p>
    <p><b>Descaling service</b> — Thermador-authorized descaling solution through boiler circuit, boiler drain verification, steam-generation sensor spec check, water valve scale-inspection. $260-$420 typical. Annual cadence for LA hard-water households.</p>
    <p><b>Boiler element replacement</b> — if deferred descaling has let scale accumulate enough to burn out the boiler element. Replacement $480-$780. The cost math strongly favors staying on descaling schedule — annual $260-$420 service versus $480-$780 element replacement roughly every 4-5 years of deferred maintenance.</p>
    <p><b>Steam-distribution valve</b> — electromechanical valve controls steam routing; failure causes incomplete steam delivery or cycle abort. Replacement $320-$540.</p>
    <p><b>Combi-mode switching logic</b> — Sapphire Steam's control firmware coordinates steam + convection in combined cycles. When firmware glitches occur, factory reset + update resolves most; control board replacement $540-$880 when not.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>BSH family — Thermador + Bosch + Gaggenau in the same LA kitchen</h2>
    <p>LA's luxury remodel market specifies BSH-family combinations routinely. Typical pattern: Thermador Masterpiece wall oven + Thermador Professional rangetop + Bosch dishwasher + sometimes a Gaggenau Vario cooktop or Gaggenau combi-steam as the ultra-luxury specialty piece. The shared BSH parent + Irvine CA parts chain means unified service infrastructure across the family — one call covers parts routing for all three brands, technical knowledge transfers between brands at the BSH-family level, and service dispatch can handle multiple BSH appliances on one visit when the failure mix allows.</p>
    <p><b>Important scope note on Bosch wall ovens specifically</b>: Bosch has a US wall oven lineup but it's not among our dedicated combo pages (per cluster-05 Decision 3, Bosch wall oven didn't hit the signal threshold for a dedicated page). For Bosch wall oven service, see the <a href="/brands/bosch/">Bosch brand hub</a> — service is fully covered through the same BSH Irvine parts chain that supports Thermador. For Gaggenau wall oven service (more common in ultra-luxury LA remodels than Bosch wall oven), see our dedicated <a href="/brands/gaggenau-wall-oven-repair/">Gaggenau wall oven combo</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common Thermador wall oven faults</h2>
    <p><b>Masterpiece bake element failure</b> — current-generation bake elements last 8-12 years typically. Replacement $380-$620.</p>
    <p><b>Professional bake element failure</b> — similar failure pattern to Masterpiece; shared parts at element level. $380-$620.</p>
    <p><b>Convection fan motor wear</b> — bearings develop play over years of thermal cycling. Replacement $440-$720.</p>
    <p><b>Temperature sensor drift</b> — cavity runs hotter or cooler than setpoint. Replacement $280-$440.</p>
    <p><b>Masterpiece control board firmware lockout</b> — factory reset + firmware update resolves some; replacement $540-$880 when not.</p>
    <p><b>Sapphire Steam descale overdue</b> — scale on boiler + plumbing. Service $260-$420.</p>
    <p><b>Door hinge wear</b> — Thermador door hinges hold up well but develop play over years. Replacement $300-$500.</p>
    <p><b>Pyrolytic self-clean cycle abort</b> — door-lock motor failure or thermal sensor drift. Diagnostic sequence.</p>
    <p><b>Double wall oven per-cavity failure</b> — upper-only or lower-only service $420-$780.</p>
  </div></section>

